OL,3,C'National priority' to get children
OL,4,Cback in school after absences treble
OL,5,Cin Wales post-pandemic
OL,7,FThe number of children persistently
OL,8,Fmissing school in Wales has more than
OL,9,Ftrebled since the Covid-19 pandemic.
OL,11,FIt's led Education Minister Jeremy
OL,12,FMiles to label the situation a
OL,13,F"national priority."
OL,15,FIn 2019, roughly one in every 20
OL,16,Fsecondary school pupils in Wales was
OL,17,Fclassed as persistently absent,
OL,18,Fmeaning they missed at least one day
OL,19,Fa week on average.
OL,21,FNow it's around one in six.
